README 

PAM-script has been written by Jeroen Nijhof <jnijhof@nijhofnet.nl>

Description:
PAM-script allows you to execute scripts during authorization, passwd changes or session.
So if you need extra work done after login you can use this pam module to execute a session script.

Customize:
If you want to customize the script names you can do that by editing the pam_script.c file.
Just change the defines...

Pam.conf example:
--- start pam.conf ---
ssh auth required	pam_script.so
ssh session required	pam_script.so
ssh passwd required	pam_script.so
--- end pam.conf ---
or for extra step:
--- start pam.conf ---
ssh auth required	pam_unix.so
ssh auth optional	pam_script.so
ssh session required	pam_unix.so
ssh session optional	pam_script.so
ssh passwd required	pam_unix.so
ssh passwd optional	pam_script.so
--- end pam.conf ---


Problem/BUGS report:
If you find any bugs or problems just mail me, Jeroen Nijhof <jnijhof@nijhofnet.nl>
